#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:477 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:475
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:490 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:491
msgid ""
"Deserts are regions of extreme dryness, making agriculture and trade very "
"difficult."
msgstr ""
"Οι ερημοι είναι περιοχές με ακραία ξηρασία , κάνοντας τη γεωργία και το "
"εμπόριο πολύ δύσκολα."

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:341 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:338
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:504 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:493
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:485 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:483
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:504 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:505
msgid "Forest"
msgstr "Δάσος"

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:380 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:377
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:547 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:536
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:526 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:524
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:547 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:548
msgid "Forests are densely wooded, making agriculture somewhat problematic."
msgstr "Τα δάση έχουν πυκνή ξυλεία, κάνοντας την γεωργία προβληματική"

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:386 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:383
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:553 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:542
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:532 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:530
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:553 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:554
msgid "Grassland"
msgstr "Χωράφι"

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:423 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:420
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:594 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:583
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:571 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:569
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:594 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:595
msgid "Grasslands afford exceptional agricultural opportunities."
msgstr "Τα χωράφια είναι εξαιρετικά για γεωργική εκμετάλλευση."

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:428 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:425
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:599 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:588
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:576 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:574
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:599 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:600
msgid "Hills"
msgstr "Λόφοι"

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:465 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:462
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:640 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:629
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:615 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:613
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:640 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:641
msgid ""
"In addition to being amenable to agriculture, Hills are frequently rich in "
"resources."
msgstr ""
"Εκτός από το ότι μπορούν να καλλιεργηθούν είναι συνήθως πλούσιοι και σε "
"πόρους."

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:468
msgid ""
"A city built in or next to hills is at risk of earthquakes, which can "
"destroy buildings in that city. There is no technology or improvement which "
"can prevent this disaster."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:475 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:468
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:649 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:635
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:621 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:619
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:649 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:650
msgid "Jungle"
msgstr "Ζούνγκλα"

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:511 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:506
#: data/classic/terrain.ruleset:677 data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:661
#: data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:659
msgid "Jungles are densely overgrown, making agriculture somewhat problematic."
msgstr ""
"Οι ζούνγκλες έχουν πυκνή βλάστηση κάνοντας την γεωργία σχετικά δύσκολη."

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:517 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:512
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:698 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:683
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:667 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:665
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:698 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:699
msgid "Mountains"
msgstr "Βουνά"

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:552 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:548
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:738 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:723
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:705 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:703
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:738 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:739
msgid ""
"Mountains are regions of extreme altitude, making agriculture and trade very "
"difficult."
msgstr ""
"Τα βουνά είναι περιοχές με μεγάλο υψόμετρο κάνοντας τη καλλιέργεια τους και "
"το εμπόριο πολύ δύσκολα."

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:555
msgid ""
"Cities built in or next to mountains are at risk from volcanic activity. A "
"Temple in the city instils sufficient respect for the forces of nature to "
"prevent population loss."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:562 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:554
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:749 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:729
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:711 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:709
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:749 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:750
msgid "Plains"
msgstr "Πεδιάδα"

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:599 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:592
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:790 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:770
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:750 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:748
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:790 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:791
msgid ""
"Plains are very broad, sparse regions, which makes trade slightly "
"inconvenient."
msgstr ""
"Οι πεδιάδες είναι πολύ πλατιές περιοχές κάνοντας το εμπόριο ελαφρός δύσκολο."

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:605 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:598
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:796 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:776
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:756 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:754
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:796 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:797
msgid "Swamp"
msgstr "Βάλτος"

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:643 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:637
#: data/classic/terrain.ruleset:819 data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:797
#: data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:795
msgid ""
"Swamps suffer from an over-abundance of water, making agriculture somewhat "
"problematic."
msgstr ""
"Οι βάλτοι έχουν υπερβολικό νερό, κάνοντας την καλλιεργειά τους σχετικά "
"προβληματική."

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:649 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:643
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:846 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:825
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:803 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:801
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:846 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:847
msgid "Tundra"
msgstr "Τούνδρα"

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:685 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:679
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:886 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:865
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:841 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:839
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:886 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:887
msgid ""
"Tundra are broad, cold regions, fit for some agriculture and little else."
msgstr ""
"Η τούνδρα είναι πλατυά κρύα περιοχή , λίγο καλλιεργίσιμη αλλά τίποτα άλλο."

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:776
#, fuzzy
msgid "?gui_type:Build Fortress"
msgstr "Χτίσε _Φρούριο"

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:779
msgid "?gui_type:Build None"
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:905 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:976
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1185 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1164
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1140 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1138
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1188 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1186
#: tools/civmanual.cpp:306
msgid "Irrigation"
msgstr "Ύδρευση"

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:919 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:991
msgid ""
"Building an irrigation system on a suitable tile causes it to produce one "
"extra food each turn. This requires a nearby source of water: an ocean or "
"river tile, or another tile with an irrigation system, must share an edge "
"(not just a corner) with the target tile. However, once irrigated, land "
"remains so even if the water source is removed."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:926 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:998
msgid "Building irrigation on a tile with a mine will destroy the mine."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:928 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:1000
msgid ""
"City center tiles get their terrain's irrigation bonus automatically, if "
"there is no conflicting mine on the tile. However, this does not make cities "
"count as a water source for further irrigation. Irrigation can be built on "
"the city tile simply to allow building further irrigation elsewhere, but "
"will not give the tile any further bonus."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:952 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:1024
msgid ""
"Mines can be built on some types of terrain, which increases the number of "
"production points produced by that tile. Hills get an extra 3 production "
"points per tile. Other terrains get 1 extra production point."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:957 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:1029
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1250 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1222
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1198 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1196
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1254 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1251
msgid "Building a mine on an irrigated tile will destroy the irrigation."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:979 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:1051
msgid ""
"Pollution appears on land tiles around cities with high production or "
"population, or when a Nuclear unit is detonated. It halves all output from "
"its tile, and contributes to the risk of global warming."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:984
msgid ""
"The pollution can only be cleared by dispatching Settlers with the \"clean "
"pollution\" order."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:987
msgid ""
"Pollution from production is likely to start becoming important as your "
"civilization becomes more industrialized, giving you buildings such as "
"Factory and Power Plant which boost production. Replacing a Power Plant with "
"cleaner forms of energy -- a Hydro Plant / Hoover Dam or Nuclear Plant -- "
"will reduce pollution from production, as will a Recycling Center."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:994
msgid ""
"The city's population starts adding to pollution with the discovery of "
"Industrialization. Automobile, Mass Production, and Plastics make this "
"worse. Building a Mass Transit in a city eliminates the population's "
"contribution to pollution."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:999 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:1071
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1349 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1291
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1267 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1266
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1353 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1350
msgid ""
"The contribution of these factors can be seen in the city dialog. Once it "
"exceeds a threshold, the excess is the percent chance of pollution appearing "
"each turn."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1003 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:1075
msgid ""
"When an unused tile becomes polluted, there is the temptation to avoid the "
"effort of cleaning it, but the spread of pollution has far more terrible "
"results than the immediate economic impact -- every polluted tile increases "
"the chance of global warming. Each time global warming advances, the entire "
"world loses coastal land to jungles and swamps, and inland tiles are lost to "
"desert. This tends to devastate cities and leads to global impoverishment."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1011
msgid ""
"The risk of global warming is cumulative. The longer polluted tiles are left "
"uncleaned, the higher the risk becomes and the risk can linger for some time "
"even after all pollution has been cleaned. If a long time passes with an "
"elevated risk of warming, its effects will be all the more severe when it "
"does occur."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1020 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:1092
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1370 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1312
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1288 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1287
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1374 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1371
msgid "Minor Tribe Village"
msgstr "Χωριό μικρής φυλής"

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1036 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:1108
msgid ""
"Villages (also called \"huts\") are primitive communities spread across the "
"world at the beginning of the game. Any land unit can enter a village, "
"making the village disappear and deliver a random response. If the village "
"proves hostile, it could produce barbarians or the unit entering may simply "
"be destroyed. If they are friendly, the player could receive gold, a new "
"technology, a military unit (occasionally a settler, and sometimes a unit "
"that the player cannot yet create), or even a new city."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1045
msgid "Flying units just fly over the village, leaving it untouched."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1050 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:1154
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1500 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1404
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1379 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1376
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1505 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1527
msgid "Fortress"
msgstr "Φρούριο"

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1073
msgid "Fortresses improve defense for land units outside cities."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1075 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:1181
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:43 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1432
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1407 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1404
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:43 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:44
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid "Diplomatic units get a 25% defense bonus in diplomatic fights."
msgstr "  * Ταχύτητα δεν επηρεάζεται από το έδαφος.\n"

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1102
msgid ""
"Roads allow your land units to move more quickly, and on some terrain also "
"provide a trade bonus."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1105 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:1242
msgid ""
"Building roads on river tiles requires knowledge of Bridge Building. City "
"center tiles automatically get roads, and are an exception to this "
"requirement."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1112 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:1249
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1706 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1551
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1528 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1523
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1670 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1741
msgid "Railroad"
msgstr "Σιδηρόδρομος"

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1135 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:1272
#: data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1574 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1546
msgid ""
"Once you learn the Railroad technology, you may upgrade your roads to "
"railroads. Units expend no movement points when moving along a railroad. You "
"may ride a railroad indefinitely. (As may your enemies!)"
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1139
msgid ""
"A railroad also increases by half (rounding down) all kinds of resources "
"produced by a tile. A tile whose road is upgraded to a railroad retains any "
"trade bonus from the road as well."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1146 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:1286
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1784 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1588
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1603 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1560
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1748 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1819
msgid "River"
msgstr "Ποταμός"

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1160
msgid "A grassland tile may have a River on it."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1162 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:1307
#: data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1608 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1580
msgid ""
"Roads and railroads can only be built on River tiles if your civilization "
"has learned Bridge Building technology."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1165
msgid ""
"Cities built on or next to rivers are at risk of flooding, which will cause "
"a loss of population and stored food. City Walls eliminate this risk."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1183 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:1324
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1828 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1625
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1645 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1597
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1792
msgid ""
"Gold is a malleable metal that has been the source of wealth for thousands "
"of years. Due to its ubiquity in nature it has traditionally been used as a "
"hard currency (coins)."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1187 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:1328
msgid ""
"Gold, when found on a Mountain tile, gives 6 more trade. For more "
"information, review the help for the individual tile type."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1193 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:1354
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1858 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1655
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1675 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1627
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1822 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1879
msgid "?animals:Game"
msgstr "?animals:Θηράματα"

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1204 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:1365
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1869 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1666
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1686 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1638
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1833
msgid ""
"Wild \"Game\" has been a source of food and tools for hunter-gathers in the "
"ancient past all the way to modern times."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1207
msgid ""
"Game, when found on a Forest or Tundra tile, gives 2 more food. For more "
"information, review the help for the individual tile types."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1213 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:1393
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1897 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1694
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1714 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1666
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1862 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1905
msgid "Coal"
msgstr "Άνθρακας"

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1224 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:1404
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1908 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1705
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1725 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1677
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1873
msgid ""
"Coal is a hard black ore that is easily mined. When burned it produces a "
"very hot fire useful for many purposes. In modern times, burning coal "
"produces the heat needed for the steam engine or to generate electricity."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1228 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:1408
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1912 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1709
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1729 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1681
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1877
msgid ""
"Coal, when found on a Hills tile, gives 2 more shields. For more "
"information, review the help for the individual tile type."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1234 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:1414
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1918 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1715
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1735 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1687
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1883 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1918
msgid "Fish"
msgstr "Ψάρι"

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1245 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:1425
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1929 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1726
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1746 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1698
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1894
msgid ""
"The fishing industry has been a source of food for all civilizations for all "
"time."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1248 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:1428
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1932 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1729
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1749 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1701
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1897
msgid ""
"Fish, when found on an Ocean tile, gives 2 more food. For more information, "
"review the help for the individual tile type."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1254 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:1454
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1958 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1755
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1775 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1727
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1923 data/sandbox/game.ruleset:2043
#: data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1944
msgid "Gems"
msgstr "Πετράδια"

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1265 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:1465
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1969 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1766
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1786 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1738
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1934
msgid ""
"Freeciv21 combines all valuable stones used in jewelry and other important "
"artifacts, such as diamonds and rubies, into the word \"gems\". These "
"precious stones have been used for trade for thousands of years."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1269 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:1469
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:1973 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1770
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1790 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1742
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1938
msgid ""
"Gems, when found on a Jungle tile, gives 4 more trade. For more information, "
"review the help for the individual tile type."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1275
msgid "Horses"
msgstr "Άλογα"

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1286
msgid "Horses have aided humans in many useful ways for thousands of years."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1288
msgid ""
"Horses, when found on a Plains tile, gives 2 more shields. For more "
"information, review the help for the individual tile type."
msgstr ""

#: data/civ1/terrain.ruleset:1294 data/civ2/terrain.ruleset:1515
#: data/civ2civ3/terrain.ruleset:2019 data/classic/terrain.ruleset:1816
#: data/experimental/terrain.ruleset:1836 data/multiplayer/terrain.ruleset:1788
#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1984 data/sandbox/terrain.ruleset:1983
msgid "Oasis"
msgstr "Όαση"

